Kim Jong Il receives Jong Ju Yong and Jong Mong Hon 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, June 30 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received Jong Ju Yong, Honorary President of the South Korean Hyundai Business Group, and Jong Mong Hon, chairman of the Hyundai Asan board of directors, in Wonsan on June 29. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On hand was Kim Yong Sun, chairman of the Korean Asia-Pacific Peace Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il warmly greeted Jong Ju Yong and Jong Mong Hon, the first visitors to the north after the inter-Korean summit, and talked with them in an amicable atmosphere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He expressed the belief that they would make a positive contribution to implementing the north-south joint declaration by pushing forward the work for national unity, reconciliation, exchange and cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   On the occasion they expressed their heartfelt thanks to him for his kind reception and encouraging words. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il arranged a dinner in honor of them and their party and had a souvenir picture taken with them.

Greetings to President of Rwanda 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 30 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, today sent a message of greetings to Paul Kagame, President of Rwanda, on its National Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It extended warm felicitations to the President, government and the people of Rwanda on the occasion of its National Day and wished the President and the people success in their work for the unity and reconciliation of the nation and stability and development of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The message expressed the belief that the friendly relations between the two countries would continue to develop on good terms.

Greetings to Burundian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 30 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, on June 28 sent a message of greetings to Pierre Buyoya, President of Burundi, on the occasion of its National Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The message extended warm felicitations to the President, government and people of Burundi on its National Day and expressed the belief that the friendly relations between the two countries would continue to develop on good terms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It wished the President and people of Burundi success in their work for peace and stability of the country.

Friendly meeting with Iranian embassy officials 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, June 30 (KCNA) -- A friendly meeting with Iranian embassy officials was held at the Pyongyang Schoolchildren's Palace on June 29 on the occasion of the establishment of a Korea-Iran friendship week. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Invited to the meeting were Iranian ambassador to the DPRK Mohammad Ganjidoost and embassy officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present there were the vice-chairman of the Korea-Iran friendship association and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The participants looked round circle rooms of the palace which serves as a center of after-school education and saw a performance given by art circle members of the palace, before talking with each other.

Independence Day of Democratic Congo commemorated here 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, June 30 (KCNA) -- A celebration meeting of the 40th anniversary of the independence of Democratic Congo was held in Pyongyang yesterday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present at the meeting were Choe Sun So, president of Kim Chol Ju University of Education and chairman of the Korea-Democratic Congo Friendship Association, association members and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the meeting a speech was made and a message of greetings to the President of the Democratic Republic of Congo was adopted.

Entourage of Jong Ju Yong inspect construction site 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, June 30 (KCNA) -- Entourage of the Honorary Chairman of the South Korean Hyundai Business Group inspected the construction site of the Pyongyang Gymnasium yesterday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the construction site the entourage including Hyundai Asan board of directors chairman Jong Mong Hon were greeted with compatriotic feelings by Song Ho Gyong, vice-chairman of the Korean Asia-Pacific Peace Committee, and officials in charge of the construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Before a layout map of the gymnasium they were briefed on preparations for the project and prospect of the construction.

Jong Ju Yong and his party leave here 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 30 (KCNA) -- Jong Ju Yong, Honorary Chairman of the South Korean Hyundai Business Group, and his party went back this morning via Panmunjom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The honorary chairman and his party were seen off at Panmunjom by Kang Jong Hun, general secretary of the Korean Asia-Pacific Peace Committee, and officials concerned with warm compatriotic feelings.

Agreement adopted at north-south Red Cross talks 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kosong, June 30 (KCNA) -- The north-south Red Cross talks, which started at Kumgangsan Hotel on June 27 to discuss humanitarian issues such as exchange of visiting groups of separated families and relatives and repatriation of unconverted long-term prisoners to mark August 15 this year in accordance with the historic north-south joint declaration closed today after adopting an agreement.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the third round of the talks both sides had earnest discussion on a draft agreement as a new proposal for sincerely implementing the north-south joint declaration was advanced again.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Both sides made a draft of the agreement on the exchange of visiting groups of separated families and relatives, repatriation of unconverted long-term prisoners and arrangement and operation of rooms for meeting and the heads of both sides separately signed it. Formally putting it into force. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  According to the agreement, the visiting groups of separated families and relatives will be exchanged simultaneously between august 15 and 18, 2000 (three nights and four days) and each group be made up of a head, one hundred separated families and relatives, 30 suite members and 20 journalists and their destination be Pyongyang and Seoul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The south side agreed to repatriate all the unconverted long-term prisoners desirous of returning to the north in early September this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It was agreed to use air and land transport services for the exchange of visiting groups and the repatriation of unconverted long-term prisoners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Both sides agreed to set up and operate meeting rooms for the separated families and relatives and discuss and decide on specific points such as  places  and date for the establishment of these rooms and  their operation immediately after the repatriation of the  prisoners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Also stipulated in the agreement are a series of working procedures related to the exchange of visiting groups of separated families and relatives and the repatriation of unconverted long-term prisoners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The adoption of the agreement on humanitarian issues at the inter-Korean Red Cross talks which were held as the first step to implement the historic north-south joint declaration after its publication amid great expectation and concern of people at home and abroad will bring new hope and joy to all the fellow countrymen and carry weighty significance in improving the relations between the north and the south of Korea.

Anniversary of Kalun meeting observed 
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 30 (KCNA) -- The Korean revolution will always advance along the road of Juche, says Rodong Sinmun today in an editorial devoted to the 70th anniversary of the Kalun meeting guided by the President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The meeting occupies a special place in the history of the Worker's Party of Korea and the Korean revolution as the principle of the Juche idea was clarified and the Juche-oriented line of the Korean revolution set forth for the first time at the meeting, the editorial says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The principle of the Juche idea and the revolutionary lines laid down at the meeting came to serve as the lifeline of the country and the nation because they put an end to the preceding national liberation movement which was moving hither and thither without a correct guiding idea and indicated the way for the Korean revolution to dynamically advance along the track of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The editorial calls for invariably holding aloft the banner of Juche which has been lifted high since the beginning of the Korean revolution no matter how much water may flow under the bridge and no matter how the conditions and circumstances of the revolutionary struggle may change. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Herein lie the source of sure victory of the Korean revolution and a firm guarantee for the final triumph of the revolutionary cause of Juche, it adds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The seven decades since the Kalun meeting are a proud history in which the Juche idea has been fully embodied in all fields of the revolution and construction and a glorious course in which the unbreakable unity and cohesion of the revolutionary ranks have been achieved on the basis of the revolutionary idea of the leader, the editorial notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean revolution has covered a long way to reach the high eminence of building a powerful nation but the spirit of the Kalun meeting has been steadfastly carried forward. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The struggle of the worker's party and people of Korea to fully embody the Juche idea in all fields of the revolution and construction has reached a new, higher phase under the energetic leadership of the respected Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The path of Juche indicated by President Kim Il Sung at the Kalun meeting is the most right path of victory and glory to be followed by the worker's party and people of Korea till the ultimate victory of the revolutionary cause of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   There can be no other way but the road of Juche for the worker's party and people of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean revolution, which was started and has dynamically advanced along the path illumined by the Juche idea, will surely achieve its ultimate victory under the banner of this idea in the future, too.

Mineral water in Korea 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 30 (KCNA) -- Korea abounds in spas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Well-known among them is mineral water in Sambang, Kwangmyong and Kangso. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Sambang and Kwangmyong mineral water is found in Sepho county and Kosan county, Kangwon Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Sambang mineral water contains 1,017.14 mg of mineral matter per litre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is listed as mineral water with the biggest amount of carbonic acid gas in the country as it contains 3,256.00 mg of free carbonate per litre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This water is good for the treatment of chronic gastritis, gastric or duodenal ulcer, hepatitis, nephritis and other diseases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Mineral water in Kwangmyong gushes out from six springs where water varies a little in its ingredients. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Its main ion ingredients are hydrogen carbonic acid, sodium and calcium. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It tastes good and is very efficacious for treating various diseases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Mineral water in nampho city gushes out from more than 10 springs. Water contains hydrogen carbonic acid with its temperature reaching 4-12 degrees centigrade and the density of its ingredient hydrogen ion 5.7-5.8. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It also tastes good and is efficacious for the treatment of a number of diseases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Also available in different parts of the country is mineral water which contains chlorine, carbonic acid, sulfur, iron and radon considered to be good for the treatment of the aftermath of operation, chronic pyelitis and cystitis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Mineral water is now being distilled and supplied to the people for the promotion of their health and modern sanatoria are operating at every spa in the DPRK.

Meeting held in Guinea to remember Kim Il Sung 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 30 (KCNA) -- A meeting for remembering the President Kim Il Sung was held by the February 16 Art Study Group of Guinean Musicians on the occasion of the 6th anniversary of his passing away. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   "The Triumphal Return" from vol. 8 (continuing edition) of part I the anti-Japanese revolution of his reminiscences "With the Century" was read at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Il Sung made great contributions to the Korean revolution and the world revolution, the head of the group said, adding: The Juche idea founded by him is now being developed in depth by the great leader Kim Jong Il and its vitality brought into bolder relief. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The participants appreciated a Korean film "Great Life in 1994."
